latestIgtvVideos.title: Voctronica - Bharat Humko Jaan Se Pyara Hai  All Vocal Tribute  #Acapella
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Voctronica Disclaimer: No Instruments were used to make this Music.

As we enter the 74th year of Independence, we wanted to take you down memory lane, to 1992, the year that this song became a feather in the Anthems that Indian cinema has produced for our diverse country. The song's message of love and unity in diversity, still hold true for the generations to come, and have even more relevance in 2020. With love in our hearts, in a true Quarantine remote attempt, we pay sincere homage to "Bharat Humko Jaan Se Pyara Hai" from "Roja" (1992), with this All Vocal Tribute.

latestIgtvVideos.caption:

latestIgtvVideos.title: Voctronica - Seven (Live) (Acoustic)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Today is the 21st day of the month, the culmination of the third week of Seven days each, and it is also a Solar eclipse that overlaps with World Music Day. As per the "Institute of Astrollogicalus", listening to purely vocal textures in the time signature of Seven (which is also the primary number of days that complete a week), three times consecutively, today, is auspicious and helps fight all negative effects. 
Check out the video below and forward it to 7 people to see the effects for yourself! Enjoy week 3, of Seven. Tu tu tududu.

#WeAreKidding #ButSeriously #ListenForBestResults #EclipseIsASevenLetterWord #SoIsSharing

P. S. This is a live acoustic version of Seven shot at Goa from slightly less stressful times, when we could jam together anywhere, and celebrate music everyday.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Voctronica - Katyusha (Live at Monks & Blues)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Missing out on the @moscowseasons Spring A Capella Festival this year, so we thought we'd share our favourite song from last year's memorable trip, performed recently at @monks_and_blues. "Katyusha" is a well known Soviet folk song, heard across Russia during their annual Victory day, and we had the honour of performing it all over the streets of Moscow, with max feels. As always, try this one with headphones, it's more enjoyable that way :) Oh and we have some BIG announcements coming soon. Stay tuned! .
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Voctronica #FanCam - 6 - Vande Mataram | All Vocal Tribute
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
On 26th January, 1950, India adopted it's Constitution and declared itself a Sovereign Socialist Secular Democratic Republic. To mark the 70th Anniversary of this historic event, here's our heartfelt #Fancam tribute celebrating this founding idea of our nation! With pride in our hearts, we give you our rendition of "Vande Mataram". There are times, when it's good to be All Vocal. Happy Republic day peeps!

#VandeMataram #AllVocal #FanCam #PlaylistThis

This version tributes an excerpt from the poem 'Vande Mataram', originally written by Shri. Bankim Chandra Chatterjee, published in his Novel 'Anandamath', and its various Musical interpretations over the years.

This FanCam is brought to you by citizens of India. .

latestIgtvVideos.title: Voctronica #FanCam - 5 - Khoya Khoya/Hawa Hawai | Live at RedBull Mumbai
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Here's a Diwali special #FanCam performance from the @redbullindia HQ, Mumbai! It mashes up two cult Bollywood/Hindi classics, and we had a lot of fun with this pop-up performance for these guys in the middle of their work space. We loved hearing the crowd sing along, so crank it up and feel free to do the same!
